HEADWORD: Mesoarium
<hw>Mes`o*a"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <grk>me`sos</grk> middle + <grk>'w,a`rion</grk>, dim. of
<grk>'w,o`n</grk> an egg.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The fold of
peritoneum which suspends the ovary from the dorsal wall of the body
cavity; the <altname>mesovarium</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
